    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>March 27/57</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir/</p>
            <p>I may as well send you<lb/> the few Dollars I have in hand.<lb/> I have been
                paid.</p>
            <p><persName>Jonas N. Phillips</persName> 3.00<lb/>
                <persName>M. Morrison</persName> 3.00 <persName>Dittenhoeffer</persName>
                <hi rend="sup">1.50</hi>/<hi rend="sub">100</hi><lb/>
                <persName>Mr H. Levy</persName>
                <hi rend="sup">1.50</hi>/<hi rend="sub">100</hi> &amp; <persName>Hy.
                    Simons</persName> 6.00 making<lb/> in all 15.00 now I have to deduct<lb/> for
                last month carriage for parcel <hi rend="sup">62</hi>/<hi rend="sub">100</hi><lb/>
                for Delivery 2100—this month <hi rend="sup">25</hi>/<hi rend="sub">100</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="sup">1.88</hi>/<hi rend="sub">100</hi> total 4.75 laid out<lb/> take off
                for the 10/ on 33.00 sent last time<lb/> without charge of <add>?</add> on
                16.00<lb/> this time 4.80. total taken off <hi rend="sup">4.75 &amp; 4.80</hi>/<hi
                    rend="sub">9.55</hi>.<lb/> 9.55 off 15.00 there remain 5.45 add to it<lb/> 10.50
                for Bible &amp; Prayer Book 10.50 it makes<lb/> in all 15.95. I have here to observe
                that <persName>Mr. H. Levy</persName> has ceased to take your<lb/> Publication also
                    <persName>Soln Weil</persName> &amp; <persName>Miss<lb/> Sarah Cohen</persName>,
                for the last I am sorry<lb/> for I think it is pressure of circumstances</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>makes her discontinue it.</p>
            <p><persName>Abm Stein</persName> also not only will not take<lb/> it but will not
                pay—he says when<lb/> he last paid you he told you not<lb/> to send it again, for he
                never reads it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">After calling a number of times<lb/> on
                    <persName>Ritterband</persName> he <sic>shewd</sic> me at last<lb/> your
                Receipts for 12.00 paid in <date>May 55</date><lb/> up to <date>March 1855</date>
                &amp; yet I hold Bills<lb/> against him for 12.00 while he only owes<lb/> 3.00 part
                of the last Bill for 2 years<lb/> I am often made to look very foolish<lb/> when so
                many dispute their accounts<lb/> &amp; in cases they are right. I look<lb/>
                anxiously for the time when you<lb/> may be here yourself to see to the<lb/> matter,
                as so many have refused to<lb/> continue taking your paper.<lb/> I really do not
                know what to<lb/> make of it—what has come over<lb/> the people. Do send the parcel
                in<lb/> time next week that the man<lb/> have time to give them out.<lb/> The last
                was not delivered till<lb/>
                <date>Saturday, the 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> last &amp; therefore<lb/> the man
                did not deliver them</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>some days afterwards</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain Dr Sir yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">M. Rubenstein</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Send in the parcel one<lb/> of your Bibles, such a one<lb/> as you sent me last,<lb/>
                but you informed me that<lb/> it was the last, &amp; I cannot<lb/> get one of
                    <persName>Mr Isaacs</persName> except<lb/> a 12 Dollar one, so if you<lb/> can
                one bound for me in time<lb/> send it, I mean the 8 Dollar one</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">M.R.</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
